<subSubSection id="62DD6540196229417486FEB8FDE4FDB0" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196229417486FEB8FE82FE77" blockId="50.[212,1172,377,599]" box="[212,320,377,400]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">
<heading id="713081A7196229417486FEB8FE82FE77" box="[212,320,377,400]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196229417486FEB8FE82FE77" box="[212,320,377,400]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196229417486FE5EFDE4FDB0" blockId="50.[212,1172,377,599]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">
The male differs from those of 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819622941761FFE61FD0DFE50" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[589,719,416,439]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guarani" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919622941761FFE61FD0DFE50" box="[589,719,416,439]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">M. guarani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2196229417689FE61FCDEFE50" box="[731,796,416,439]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819622941770CFE61FC32FE5F" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[862,1008,416,440]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karitiana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919622941770CFE61FC32FE5F" box="[862,1008,416,440]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">M. karitiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A21962294177AEFE61FBFFFE50" box="[1020,1085,416,439]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the digitiform medial protruding process of S4, in lateral view; from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481962294177E2FE01FB97FE30" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[944,1109,448,471]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mapinguari" status="sp. n">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91962294177E2FE01FB97FE30" box="[944,1109,448,471]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">M. mapinguari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A219622941700CFE01FB51FE30" box="[1118,1171,448,471]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" rank="species">sp. n</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48196229417557FE21FE46FE10" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[261,388,480,503]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavante" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196229417557FE21FE46FE10" box="[261,388,480,503]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">M. xavante</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A21962294175DEFE21FE0BFE10" box="[396,457,480,503]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the mesosoma homogeneously blackish (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1962294177EDFE1EFB85FE10" box="[959,1095,479,503]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="19.[144,213,1405,1427]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[144,1104,168,1373]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 11. Males of Megalopta. (A, C, D). Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. karitiana sp. n. from Ouro Preto do Oeste, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (D) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (E) dorsal view of mesosoma of M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (F) posterior view of mesosoma of M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004481/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">Figures 11F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E196229417004FE1EFB46FE10" box="[1110,1156,479,503]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="20.[212,279,1400,1422]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[212,1172,168,1368]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 12. Males of Megalopta. (A‒C) Habitus, dorsal view; (A) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. purpurata (holotype) Smith from Tefé, Brazil; (D‒F) posterolateral view of mesosoma; (D) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (E) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (F) M. munduruku sp. n. from Belterra, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004483/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">12C</figureCitation>
); also distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481962294175B8FDC1FD51FDF0" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[490,659,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mapinguari">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91962294175B8FDC1FD51FDF0" box="[490,659,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">M. mapinguari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by medial protruding process of S4 lacking setae in the apex; from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481962294175BAFDE1FDB6FDD0" authorityName="Santos and Silveira" authorityYear="2009" box="[488,628,543,567]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91962294175BAFDE1FDB6FDD0" box="[488,628,543,567]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">M. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of rugulosities in basal area of metapostnotum (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1962294175C7FDFEFDD4FDB0" box="[405,534,575,599]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="20.[212,279,1400,1422]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[212,1172,168,1368]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 12. Males of Megalopta. (A‒C) Habitus, dorsal view; (A) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. purpurata (holotype) Smith from Tefé, Brazil; (D‒F) posterolateral view of mesosoma; (D) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (E) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (F) M. munduruku sp. n. from Belterra, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004483/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">Figure 12C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
