The 
<typeStatus id="F57C8869196229417559FBB7FEF9FB69" box="[267,315,1142,1166]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">type</typeStatus>
was not examined directly, but through photographs obtained from the British Museum (
<collectionCode id="4CD6AE0E1962294175CBFB54FE37FB4A" box="[409,501,1173,1197]" pageId="50" pageNumber="625">BMNH</collectionCode>
). Its inclusion in the byroni species group was based on the following features: body coloration without metallic green reflections and S 
<quantity id="ED3F9B2E196229417074FB74FB90FB2A" box="[1062,1106,1205,1229]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="50" pageNumber="625" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
basal area with a digitiform medial protruding process. Some characteristics of this species were extracted from Moure’ s (1958) redescription
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
